  footnotes: []
english:
  title: The Ancient Willow
  author: Kim Si-seup
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The ancient willow thrums with cicada song,
    and in this distant land, my heart grows strange.
    Through sparse rain, the river gleams half-bright,
    while layered peaks emerge in jade.

    The long day draws me to move my writing desk,
    and clear spring water washes out wine jugs.
    Few visitors come to call these days—
    growing ever more forlorn, I have no purpose left.
  footnotes:
    - The poem expresses the melancholy of exile or separation from home, a common theme in East Asian classical poetry. The natural imagery—the cicadas, rain, river, and spring—mirrors the speaker's emotional state of displacement and gradual withdrawal from society.
